Condition: What is the effect on herring?

C: The fishing of small pelagics increased therefore the population of herring decreased.

Condition: What is the effect on winter flounder?

C: The Winter flounder population increased a lot because the fishing effort was halved

Condition: What is the effect on yellowtail flounder?

C: There is competition between the other two types of flatfish and because the population of the other two grew so much, there was not a lot of room for the yellowtail flounder population to grow.

Condition: What is the effect on skates?

C: The fishing efforts doubled therefore the population of skates dropped dramatically.

Condition: What is the effect on cod?

C: Dogfish prey on cod, so if the population of dogfish dropped dramatically then the population of cod will increase.

Condition: What is the effect on haddock?

C: Haddock compete directly with cod so if Cod populations explode then the haddock population will drop a little bit.

Condition: What is the effect on windowpane?

C: Cod compete with Windowpane, so if the cod population increases than there will be less food for the windowpane population and it will decrease.
